CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 1, 1954, pg. 6, reads: "Tree Falls Across Webster Avenue - During Tuesday night's thunderstorm this tree was blown down, completely covering this automobile parked in the 2900 block of Webster Avenue.  Police reported that the car is owned by Central Baptist Church.  The tree also blocked traffic on Webster Avenue for five hours until it was removed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Large tree fallen on car after storm, 2900 block of Webster Avenue, Hill District
